            "body": "> Automated screenshot testing. In particular in 'mini.test'.\n\n`nvim__screenshot` (experimental) ?\n\n> No, there is no stable and documented alternatives.\n\nI would say that attaching a UI similar to [screen.lua](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/772f1966a348eb26bc9cb17d45bbdb739642ccdb/test/functional/ui/screen.lua#L181) is the recommended way to write screen tests.\n\nBut yes, we need to expose that. https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/34592\n\nhttps://github.com/lewis6991/nvim-test has a screen module...",
